-- FibreCo Builds $605 Million Network, Bus. Report Says
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2012-07-09T09:16:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/fibreco-building-605-million-network-business-report-says.html
(Corrects name of FibreCo shareholder in third paragraph.)  FibreCo Telecommunications Ltd.  is
spending 5 billion rand ($605 million) building a fiber-optic
network linking the coastal cities of  Cape Town , East London and
Durban with Johannesburg,  Business Report  said, citing Chief
Executive Officer Arif Hussain.  Construction started in April and will result in an open-
access 12,000-kilometer (7,460-mile) network, the Johannesburg-
based newspaper said.  FibreCo is a joint venture between Cell C (Pty) Ltd., the
nation’s third-largest mobile-phone operator, Dimension Data
Holdings Plc’s Internet Solutions unit and Convergence Partners
(Pty) Ltd., according to information on FibreCo’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story: Sikonathi Mantshantsha in
Johannesburg at   sikonathim@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Kenneth Wong
at   kwong11@bloomberg.net  